                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4311.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador and to the American Consul at
                            Ciudad Juárez</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-19T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Governor of Texas informs War Department of indications that a Federal force,
                    now approaching Ciudad Juárez, intends to recapture it. In that event bullets
                    might pass across boundary and endanger American citizens on American soil.
                    Bring this immediately <pb facs="1000" n="884" xml:id="pg_884"/> to attention
                    President Madero and Foreign Office. Very strongly urge instructions to attack
                    so as to avoid firing across the line. If this risk can not be avoided during
                    attack, suggest very urgently that attack be postponed until better opportunity
                    to capture the city offers; do this as under specific instructions from the
                    President. Suggest possibly equally effective siege operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
